name: Rise
description:
Letterpress print
6.5” x 4.75”

Hand printed on 100% rag paper
Supplied in acid free mount, unframed
Limited edition of 20


Hand drawn and hand printed, this artwork is inspired from a season spent fly fishing on a beautiful chalk stream in south west England: Cool waters, warm breezes, green fields, and glimpses of bejeweled wild trout in crystal pools.

The frame in the photos is not included. I ship all prints with an acid free mount, ready for framing, and plenty of protection.

name: Something in angling
description:
Giclee print
6.5” x 4.75”

Printed to Fine Art Trade Guilds standards
Somerset Velvet Enhanced 255gsm, 100% rag paper
Light fast, pigmented ink
Unframed but supplied in mount as shown
Fits a 10" x 12" frame


"There is certainly something in angling that tends to produce a serenity of the mind." ~ Washington Irving

This is one of a set of 4 prints that is themed around my favourite fishing quotes. Each quote is set into a hand drawn illustration, inspired by a wonderful start to this year's fishing season on our beautiful English chalk stream.
